{"title_page": "1963\u201364 West Midlands (Regional) League", "text_new": "{{Infobox football league season\n|competition = West Midlands<br>(Regional) League\n|season=1963\u201364\n|winners=[[Tamworth F.C.|Tamworth]]\n|promoted=\n|relegated=\n|matches=342\n|total goals=1293\n|prevseason= [[1962\u201363 West Midlands (Regional) League|1962\u201363]]\n|nextseason= [[1964\u201365 West Midlands (Regional) League|1964\u201365]]\n}}\nThe '''1963\u201364 West Midlands (Regional) League season''' was the 64th in the history of the [[West Midlands (Regional) League]], an English [[association football]] competition for semi-professional and amateur teams based in the [[West Midlands (county)|West Midlands county]], [[Shropshire]], [[Herefordshire]], [[Worcestershire]] and southern [[Staffordshire]].\n\n==Clubs==\nThe league featured 18 clubs from the previous season, along with one new club:\n*[[Gornal Athletic F.C.|Lower Gornal Athletic]], joined from the [[Worcestershire Combination]]\n\n===League table===\n<onlyinclude>{{#invoke:Sports table|main|style=WDL\n|use_goal_ratio=y\n|winpoints=2\n|res_col_header=PR\n\n|team1=TAM|name_TAM=[[Tamworth F.C.|Tamworth]]\n|team2=KID|name_KID=[[Kidderminster Harriers F.C.|Kidderminster Harriers]]\n|team3=HAL|name_HAL=[[Halesowen Town F.C.|Halesowen Town]]\n|team4=BRO|name_BRO=[[Bromsgrove Rovers F.C.|Bromsgrove Rovers]]\n|team5=DUD|name_DUD=[[Dudley Town F.C.|Dudley Town]]\n|team6=STO|name_STO=[[Stourbridge F.C.|Stourbridge]]\n|team7=HED|name_HED=[[Hednesford Town F.C.|Hednesford]]\n|team8=BIL|name_BIL=[[Bilston Town F.C.|Bilston]]\n|team9=BAN|name_BAN=[[Banbury United F.C.|Banbury Spencer]]\n|team10=ATH|name_ATH=[[Atherstone Town F.C.|Atherstone Town]]\n|team11=BHA|name_BHA=[[Brierley Hill Alliance F.C.|Brierley Hill Alliance]]\n|team12=GOR|name_GOR=[[Gornal Athletic F.C.|Lower Gornal Athletic]]\n|team13=LYE|name_LYE=[[Lye Town F.C.|Lye Town]]\n|team14=DAR|name_DAR=[[Darlaston F.C.|Darlaston]]\n|team15=STA|name_STA=[[Stratford Town F